title: Problem with refining my tracklets
body:
Hello dear DeepLabCut-Team I have been trying to reach the "refine tracklets" register for over 4 weeks now, but I always reach new problems and I feel like this time I really reached my limit, so I hope you can somehow help me (I'm a total noob and feel like barely scraping by ^^) **I'm working on Windows 10, using DeepLabCut 2.1.10.4 and using the GUI-version of multi-animal estimation. I work over anaconda, using the GPU-Env. (GeForce GTX970, which is so weak I have to work with a batchsize of 4 and a global scale of 0.4) Please complete the following information about your system: OS: Windows 10 DeepLabCut Version: 2.1.10.4 (according to anaconda) Anaconda env used: GPU Actually I have even a problem to really see where the problem lies, so let me try to explain where I am at right now. I trained a multianimal-system to recognize the upper body-movement (Shoulder, Elbow, Arm, Wrist and Index-Finger) of 3 different people (2 important, third being the experimenter). Anyways, it seemed to me, like everything was finally working. I did train my network and when looking at the video for detection-checking, it seemed like it was mostly working (with some need for additional refinement, but still finding the important joints). When going for refinement though, DLC doesn't show any tracklets all the sudden. Thinking this might be because of a weak model I did evaluate once more, but I can't understand the meaning of the output and even worse: Yesterday after training the AI I can't remember it looking so suspicious. SO now my problem is, that I can't even tell anymore where the fault might be, as it appears like everything changed once more when trying to evaluate again today.
